main event: CPO Delbert C. Newhouse reported seeing a group of objects milling about in rough formation while driving on the highway.
interesting points: The sighting took place 7 miles north of Tremonton, Utah, The group of objects had no reference points for speed, distance, or size estimation, The objects were too small in the photo to show detail, The explanation given for the objects included pillow balloons or birds, The report includes 5 photographs of the sighted objects.
sighted object: a group of unknown objects in rough formation
witness description: CPO Delbert C. Newhouse and his wife
